@startuml
' @id(CMP-AGENT-PREPARE)
' @desc(CMP-AGENT-PREPARE, "The `mdd agent` subcommand in crates/mdd-cli/src/main.rs: the Commands::Agent { kind: String } variant and its match arm. The arm discovers the Project, maps the kind string through AgentKind::parse, and delegates to mdd_agent::prepare_agent — it adds no new behaviour, only a CLI entry point, mirroring Commands::Validate / Commands::Context as thin presentation over a core crate. This makes mdd-agent (previously an orphan workspace crate with no caller) a real mdd-cli dependency and closes its mapping gap.")
title MDD agent prepare CLI — ownership (objective)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev

component "mdd agent --kind\n(CMP-AGENT-PREPARE)\nmdd-cli/src/main.rs" as Cli
component "prepare_agent / AgentKind\n(mdd-agent crate)" as Agent
component "AgentPreparationReport\n{instruction_file, hooks_run}" as Report

Dev --> Cli : mdd agent --kind <agent>
Cli --> Agent : prepare_agent(&project, kind)
Agent --> Report : instruction_file + hooks_run
Cli --> Report : read for stdout

note bottom of Cli
  Thin presentation layer like Commands::Validate. mdd-agent
  becomes a declared mdd-cli dependency; behaviour stays in
  the crate. No new engine.
end note
@enduml
